Title: Zeta function determinant of the Laplace operator on the $D$-dimensional
  ball
Author: M. Bordag, B. Geyer, K. Kirsten (Institute for Theoretical Physics,
  Leipzig University, Germany) and E. Elizalde (CEAB, CSIC, Cam\'{\i} de Santa
  B\`arbara and Departament d'ECM and IFAE, Facultat de F{\ii}sica, Universitat
  de Barcelona, Spain)
Comments: 22 pages, one figure appended as uuencoded postscript file
Report-no: UB-ECM-PF 95/10
Journal-ref: Commun.Math.Phys. 179 (1996) 215-234
\\
  We present a direct approach for the calculation of functional determinants
of the Laplace operator on balls. Dirichlet and Robin boundary conditions are
considered. Using this approach, formulas for any value of the dimension, $D$,
of the ball, can be obtained quite easily. Explicit results are presented here
for dimensions $D=2,3,4,5$ and $6$.
